# DedgeAuth Solution — Log File Locations

All log paths are relative to `%OptPath%` (typically `E:\opt` on servers, `C:\opt` on dev machines). The relative folder is configured in each project's `appsettings.json` and joined with `%OptPath%` at runtime.

## DedgeAuth.Api

| Item | Value |
|---|---|
| Config key | `LogFileSettings:LogFolder` |
| Config value | `data\DedgeAuth.Api` |
| File pattern | `DedgeAuth-YYYYMMDD.log` (Serilog daily rolling) |
| Retention | 31 files |

| Environment | Local path | UNC path |
|---|---|---|
| **TST** | `E:\opt\data\DedgeAuth.Api\DedgeAuth-YYYYMMDD.log` | `C:\opt\src\DedgeSrc\DedgeSystemTools\Folders\Opt\data\DedgeAuth.Api\DedgeAuth-YYYYMMDD.log` |
| **PRD** | `E:\opt\data\DedgeAuth.Api\DedgeAuth-YYYYMMDD.log` | `\\p-no1fkxprd-app\Opt\data\DedgeAuth.Api\DedgeAuth-YYYYMMDD.log` |
| **Dev** | `C:\opt\data\DedgeAuth.Api\DedgeAuth-YYYYMMDD.log` | (local only) |

## IIS-AutoDeploy.Tray

| Item | Value |
|---|---|
| Config key | `IIS-AutoDeploy:LogFolder` |
| Config value | `data\IIS-AutoDeploy.Tray` |
| File pattern | `IIS-AutoDeploy.Tray-YYYYMMDD.log` (daily rolling) |

| Environment | Local path | UNC path |
|---|---|---|
| **TST** | `E:\opt\data\IIS-AutoDeploy.Tray\IIS-AutoDeploy.Tray-YYYYMMDD.log` | `C:\opt\src\DedgeSrc\DedgeSystemTools\Folders\Opt\data\IIS-AutoDeploy.Tray\IIS-AutoDeploy.Tray-YYYYMMDD.log` |
| **PRD** | `E:\opt\data\IIS-AutoDeploy.Tray\IIS-AutoDeploy.Tray-YYYYMMDD.log` | `\\p-no1fkxprd-app\Opt\data\IIS-AutoDeploy.Tray\IIS-AutoDeploy.Tray-YYYYMMDD.log` |
| **Dev** | `C:\opt\data\IIS-AutoDeploy.Tray\IIS-AutoDeploy.Tray-YYYYMMDD.log` | (local only) |

## Quick Access (PowerShell)

```powershell
# Today's DedgeAuth.Api log on TST
$today = Get-Date -Format 'yyyyMMdd'
Copy-Item "C:\opt\src\DedgeSrc\DedgeSystemTools\Folders\Opt\data\DedgeAuth.Api\DedgeAuth-$($today).log" $env:TEMP -Force
code "$env:TEMP\DedgeAuth-$($today).log"

# Today's IIS-AutoDeploy.Tray log on TST
Copy-Item "C:\opt\src\DedgeSrc\DedgeSystemTools\Folders\Opt\data\IIS-AutoDeploy.Tray\IIS-AutoDeploy.Tray-$($today).log" $env:TEMP -Force
code "$env:TEMP\IIS-AutoDeploy.Tray-$($today).log"
```

## Convention

When adding new projects to this solution, follow the same pattern:
1. Add `"LogFolder": "data\\<ProjectName>"` to `appsettings.json`
2. Join `%OptPath%` + config value at runtime to form the log directory
3. Never hardcode absolute log paths in code
